18/11/2005
STRASBOURG, France -- Effective Thursday (17 November), Romania officially took over the six-month rotating presidency of the Council of Europe's Committee of Ministers, replacing Portugal. Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu said his country's presidency would focus on strengthening the Council's system of human rights protection, as well as strengthening efforts to promote democracy, build a more humane Europe, and boost co-operation among the Council of Europe, the EU and OSCE.
In other news, Romanian President Traian Basescu called a rare meeting Friday of the country's Supreme Defence Council. Local media reports suggest he is planning significant staff changes within the Intelligence Service, the Foreign Intelligence Service, the Special Transmissions Service and the Guard and Protection Service. (Nine o'Clock - 18/11/05; Rompres - 17/11/05)
